# Sergey Feldman | Semantic Scholar

[

## SPECTER: Document-level Representation Learning using Citation-informed Transformers

](/paper/SPECTER%3A-Document-level-Representation-Learning-Cohan-Feldman/a3e4ceb42cbcd2c807d53aff90a8cb1f5ee3f031)

[Arman Cohan](/author/Arman-Cohan/2527954)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)[Iz Beltagy](/author/Iz-Beltagy/46181066)[Doug Downey](/author/Doug-Downey/145612610)[Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531)

Computer Science

-   15 April 2020

This work proposes SPECTER, a new method to generate document-level embedding of scientific papers based on pretraining a Transformer language model on a powerful signal of document- level relatedness: the citation graph, and shows that Specter outperforms a variety of competitive baselines on the benchmark.

[

## Construction of the Literature Graph in Semantic Scholar

](/paper/Construction-of-the-Literature-Graph-in-Semantic-Ammar-Groeneveld/649def34f8be52c8b66281af98ae884c09aef38b)

[Bridger Waleed Ammar](/author/Bridger-Waleed-Ammar/145585097)[Dirk Groeneveld](/author/Dirk-Groeneveld/3458736) [Oren Etzioni](/author/Oren-Etzioni/1741101)

Computer Science

-   6 May 2018

This paper reduces literature graph construction into familiar NLP tasks, point out research challenges due to differences from standard formulations of these tasks, and report empirical results for each task.

[

## Content-Based Citation Recommendation

](/paper/Content-Based-Citation-Recommendation-Bhagavatula-Feldman/921b2958cac4138d188fd5047aa12bbcf37ac867)

[Chandra Bhagavatula](/author/Chandra-Bhagavatula/1857797)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)[Russell Power](/author/Russell-Power/39071178)[Bridger Waleed Ammar](/author/Bridger-Waleed-Ammar/145585097)

Computer Science

-   22 February 2018

It is shown empirically that, although adding metadata improves the performance on standard metrics, it favors self-citations which are less useful in a citation recommendation setup and released an online portal for citation recommendation based on this method.

[

## SciRepEval: A Multi-Format Benchmark for Scientific Document Representations

](/paper/SciRepEval%3A-A-Multi-Format-Benchmark-for-Scientific-Singh-D'Arcy/0d68e244faa9a5944228b571d91bc7bed88083cd)

[Amanpreet Singh](/author/Amanpreet-Singh/2116287642)[Mike D'Arcy](/author/Mike-D'Arcy/40480862)[Arman Cohan](/author/Arman-Cohan/2527954)[Doug Downey](/author/Doug-Downey/145612610)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)

Computer Science, Biology

-   23 November 2022

It is shown how state-of-the-art models like SPECTER and SciNCL struggle to generalize across the task formats, and that simple multi-task training fails to improve them, and a new approach that learns multiple embeddings per document, each tailored to a different format, can improve performance.

[

## The Semantic Scholar Open Data Platform

](/paper/The-Semantic-Scholar-Open-Data-Platform-Kinney-Anastasiades/cb92a7f9d9dbcf9145e32fdfa0e70e2a6b828eb1)

[Rodney Michael Kinney](/author/Rodney-Michael-Kinney/143967880)[Chloe Anastasiades](/author/Chloe-Anastasiades/1667818755) [Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531)

Computer Science

-   2023

This paper combines public and proprietary data sources using state-of-theart techniques for scholarly PDF content extraction and automatic knowledge graph construction to build the Semantic Scholar Academic Graph, the largest open scientific literature graph to-date.

[

## ABNIRML: Analyzing the Behavior of Neural IR Models

](/paper/ABNIRML%3A-Analyzing-the-Behavior-of-Neural-IR-Models-MacAvaney-Feldman/402954647b4a4855ccbe953c762518b90c7557c0)

[Sean MacAvaney](/author/Sean-MacAvaney/22214396)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)[Nazli Goharian](/author/Nazli-Goharian/1685063)[Doug Downey](/author/Doug-Downey/145612610)[Arman Cohan](/author/Arman-Cohan/2527954)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   2 November 2020

A new comprehensive framework for Analyzing the Behavior of Neural IR ModeLs (ABNIRML) is presented, which includes new types of diagnostic probes that allow us to test several characteristics—such as writing styles, factuality, sensitivity to paraphrasing and word order—that are not addressed by previous techniques.

[

## RCT Rejection Sampling for Causal Estimation Evaluation

](/paper/RCT-Rejection-Sampling-for-Causal-Estimation-Keith-Feldman/f2410b3da60ba080031d50b6e2217003173c0eb0)

[Katherine A. Keith](/author/Katherine-A.-Keith/145137850)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)[David Jurgens](/author/David-Jurgens/3046220)[Jonathan Bragg](/author/Jonathan-Bragg/2699105)[Rohit Bhattacharya](/author/Rohit-Bhattacharya/40107797)

Computer Science, Medicine

Trans. Mach. Learn. Res.

-   27 July 2023

This work builds on a promising empirical evaluation strategy that simplifies evaluation design and uses real data: subsampling randomized controlled trials (RCTs) to create confounded observational datasets while using the average causal effects from the RCTs as ground-truth.

[

## Overview of the TREC 2020 Fair Ranking Track

](/paper/Overview-of-the-TREC-2020-Fair-Ranking-Track-Biega-Diaz/f3e2b635a3a554f9a4d61510b37c728c15f82efb)

[Asia J. Biega](/author/Asia-J.-Biega/2133238109)[Fernando Diaz](/author/Fernando-Diaz/145472333)[Michael D. Ekstrand](/author/Michael-D.-Ekstrand/2386667)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)[Sebastian Kohlmeier](/author/Sebastian-Kohlmeier/41018147)

Computer Science

-   11 August 2021

The track contains two tasks,reranking and retrieval, with a shared evaluation, and expected participants to develop systems that optimize for fairness and relevance for arbitrary group definitions.

[

## Completely Lazy Learning

](/paper/Completely-Lazy-Learning-Garcia-Feldman/99cdd7de3b042b5234d1db795c39c1039fa3efe4)

[Eric K. Garcia](/author/Eric-K.-Garcia/2111323476)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)[M. Gupta](/author/M.-Gupta/9595724)[S. Srivastava](/author/S.-Srivastava/47018671)

Computer Science

-   1 September 2010

This work proposes a simple alternative to cross validation of the neighborhood size that requires no preprocessing: instead of committing to one neighborhood size, average the discriminants for multiple neighborhoods so that similar classification performance can be attained without any training.

[

## Simplified Data Wrangling with ir\_datasets

](/paper/Simplified-Data-Wrangling-with-ir_datasets-MacAvaney-Yates/387d17e3bc44ed4f81de25fc27fa1b8ab7d6bc8d)

[Sean MacAvaney](/author/Sean-MacAvaney/22214396)[Andrew Yates](/author/Andrew-Yates/144115896)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)[Doug Downey](/author/Doug-Downey/145612610)[Arman Cohan](/author/Arman-Cohan/2527954)[Nazli Goharian](/author/Nazli-Goharian/1685063)

Computer Science

-   3 March 2021

A new robust and lightweight tool for acquiring, managing, and performing typical operations over datasets used in IR, primarily focus on textual datasets used for ad-hoc search.
